# The project provides a demonstartion of implementing a simple docker integration test
There are 2 pom files we have used - 
1. "pom-self.xml"  is used as standalone and 
2. "pom-parent.cml" is inheriting from ots ejava-build-parent pom.xml file

We have modofied the pom-parent.xml as required to accomplish the goal. The original file in the 
Gitlab repository was not enough to accomplish all the task describe un the chapter Docker Integration test

Make the test in the CI/CD environment you need to add the environment variable from windows powershell as follows - 

Set the value: Use the $env: prefix with the assignment operator.

$env:TESTCONTAINERS_HOST_OVERRIDE = "host.docker.internal"

Show the value: Simply type the variable name to display it in the console.

$env:TESTCONTAINERS_HOST_OVERRIDE


# Remove from current session
Remove-Item Env:TESTCONTAINERS_HOST_OVERRIDE


